description:
This example demonstrates how to use loadJSON()
  to retrieve data from a JSON file and make objects 
  from that data.

  Here is what the JSON looks like (partial):

 {
 "bubbles": [
 {
 "position": {
 "x": 160,
 "y": 103
 },
 "diameter": 43.19838,
 "label": "Happy"
 },
 {
 "position": {
 "x": 372,
 "y": 137
 },
 "diameter": 52.42526,
 "label": "Sad"
 }
 ]
 }
